# MUI Mobile Design Rules

## 📱 **Mobile Container Pattern**

**ALWAYS** use this exact container pattern for every page:

```jsx
<Box sx={{
  width: '375px',
  height: '812px',
  margin: '40px auto',
  overflow: 'hidden',
  backgroundColor: '#f8fafc',
  minHeight: '100vh',
  display: 'flex',
  flexDirection: 'column',
}}>
  {/* Page content */}
</Box>
```

## 🎨 **MUI Component Usage**

### **Layout Components**
```jsx
// ALWAYS use these for layout
import { Box, Container, Grid, Paper } from '@mui/material';

// For flexible layouts
<Box sx={{ display: 'flex', gap: 2, p: 3 }}>

// For page containers
<Container maxWidth="lg" sx={{ py: 4 }}>

// For responsive grids
<Grid container spacing={2}>
  <Grid item xs={12} md={6}>
```

### **Typography**
```jsx
// ALWAYS use semantic variants
<Typography variant="h4" component="h1">Main Heading</Typography>
<Typography variant="body1" color="text.secondary">Body text</Typography>
<Typography variant="caption">Small text</Typography>
```

### **Buttons**
```jsx
// Primary actions
<Button variant="contained" startIcon={<Add />}>
  Add Observation
</Button>

// Secondary actions
<Button variant="outlined" startIcon={<Save />}>
  Save Draft
</Button>

// Text buttons for less important actions
<Button variant="text" color="error">
  Delete
</Button>
```

### **Cards**
```jsx
<Card sx={{ borderRadius: 2 }}>
  <CardContent>
    <Typography variant="h6">Card Title</Typography>
    <Typography variant="body2">Card content</Typography>
  </CardContent>
  <CardActions>
    <Button size="small">Action</Button>
  </CardActions>
</Card>
```

### **Forms**
```jsx
// Text inputs
<TextField
  fullWidth
  label="Observation Text"
  multiline
  rows={4}
  placeholder="Enter your observation..."
/>

// Select dropdowns
<FormControl fullWidth>
  <InputLabel>Curriculum Area</InputLabel>
  <Select value={value} label="Curriculum Area">
    <MenuItem value="practical-life">Practical Life</MenuItem>
    <MenuItem value="language">Language</MenuItem>
  </Select>
</FormControl>
```

## 🚫 **What NOT to Do**

### **NEVER use inline styles**
```jsx
// ❌ WRONG
<div style={{ padding: '16px', backgroundColor: 'white' }}>

// ✅ CORRECT
<Box sx={{ p: 2, backgroundColor: 'white' }}>
```

### **NEVER exceed 375px width**
```jsx
// ❌ WRONG
<Box sx={{ width: '500px' }}>

// ✅ CORRECT
<Box sx={{ width: '375px' }}>
```

### **NEVER use custom CSS classes**
```jsx
// ❌ WRONG
<div className="custom-styles">

// ✅ CORRECT
<Box sx={{ /* styles here */ }}>
```

## 📱 **Mobile-First Responsive Patterns**

### **Hide elements on mobile**
```jsx
<Typography sx={{ display: { xs: 'none', sm: 'block' } }}>
  Desktop only text
</Typography>
```

### **Stack vertically on mobile**
```jsx
<Box sx={{ 
  flexDirection: { xs: 'column', md: 'row' },
  gap: { xs: 1, md: 2 }
}}>
```

### **Touch-friendly sizing**
```jsx
// Minimum 44px for touch targets
<IconButton sx={{ minWidth: 44, minHeight: 44 }}>
  <Settings />
</IconButton>
```

## 🎯 **Theme Colors**

**ALWAYS** use theme colors instead of hardcoded values:

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<Typography color="text.secondary">Secondary text</Typography>
<Button color="primary">Primary action</Button>
<Alert severity="error">Error message</Alert>

// ❌ WRONG
<Typography sx={{ color: '#64748b' }}>Hardcoded color</Typography>
```

## 🔧 **Accessibility Requirements**

### **Always include aria-labels**
```jsx
<IconButton aria-label="Start recording">
  <Mic />
</IconButton>

<Button aria-label="Delete observation">
  <Delete />
</Button>
```

### **Use semantic HTML**
```jsx
<Typography component="h1" variant="h4">
  Page Title
</Typography>
```

## 📏 **Spacing System**

Use MUI's spacing system (8px base):
- `1` = 8px
- `2` = 16px  
- `3` = 24px
- `4` = 32px

```jsx
<Box sx={{ p: 2, m: 1, gap: 2 }}>
  <Typography sx={{ mb: 2 }}>Content</Typography>
</Box>
```

## 🎨 **Icons**

**ALWAYS** use Material Icons from `@mui/icons-material`:

```jsx
import { Mic, Stop, PlayArrow, Settings, Delete } from '@mui/icons-material';

<IconButton>
  <Mic />
</IconButton>
```

